4. 🧠 Core Components

4.1 Orchestrator Engine (Central Brain)

Responsibilities:

* Workflow coordination
* State transitions
* Retry & loop control
* Decision making

Recommended Tech:

* Phase 1 (PoC): FastAPI + Redis Queue
* Phase 2 (Enterprise): Temporal / Cadence (JPMC-aligned)

⸻

4.2 Agent Layer (Role Replacement)

Role	Agent	Function
Product Owner	Planner Agent	HLDD → Epics/Stories
Tech Lead	Dev Agent	Code generation
Reviewer	Review Agent	PR validation
QA	Test Agent	Unit/integration tests
SRE	Validation Agent	Post-deploy checks

⸻

4.3 Integration Layer

Jira

* REST API (create/update issues)
* Webhooks → Event Bus

GitHub

* PR creation
* Webhooks for:
    * PR opened
    * PR updated
    * PR comments

CI/CD

* GitHub Actions / Jenkins
* Emits deployment events

⸻

4.4 Event Bus

Purpose:

* Decouple systems
* Enable async processing

Options:

* Kafka (enterprise preferred)
* AWS SNS/SQS
* RabbitMQ (PoC)

⸻

4.5 State Store

Tracks:

* Task lifecycle
* Agent execution state
* Iteration count

Tech:

* PostgreSQL (recommended)
* Redis (for caching)

⸻

4.6 Policy Engine

Enforces:

* Who can trigger what
* What AI can/cannot do

Options:

* OPA (Open Policy Agent)
* Cedar (AWS-style)

⸻

5. 🔄 End-to-End Workflow

Phase 1: Planning

1. HLDD ingested
2. Planner Agent generates:
    * Epics
    * Stories
    * Tasks
    * Sprint allocation
3. Jira tickets created

⸻

Phase 2: Development

Trigger:

* Jira status → “In Progress”

Flow:

1. Webhook → Event Bus
2. Orchestrator triggers Dev Agent
3. Dev Agent:
    * Generates code
    * Pushes branch
    * Creates PR

⸻

Phase 3: Review Loop

1. GitHub PR webhook triggers Review Agent
2. Review Agent:
    * Adds comments
3. Orchestrator:
    * Sends feedback to Dev Agent
4. Loop continues until:
    * Approval OR max iterations reached

⸻

Phase 4: CI/CD

1. PR approved → merge
2. CI/CD pipeline runs:
    * build
    * test
    * deploy

⸻

Phase 5: Post-Deployment

Trigger:

* Deployment event

Validation Agent:

* API tests
* smoke tests
* health checks

⸻

6. 🔐 Security & Compliance (Critical for JPMC)

Data Protection

* No sensitive data in prompts
* Masking + tokenization

Access Control

* RBAC for:
    * agents
    * APIs

Audit Logging

* Store:
    * prompts
    * outputs
    * decisions

Model Governance

* Approved model registry
* Version tracking

⸻

